<subSubSection id="C33B90F7447FFF80646538BFFABBFA91" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9EC37C447FFF80646538BFFC60FD90" blockId="3.[806,1421,508,591]" box="[806,925,508,529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">
<emphasis id="B9551F6E447FFF80646538BFFC60FD90" box="[806,925,508,529]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EC37C447FFF8064653B59FB58FDCE" blockId="3.[806,1421,508,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">
The name of the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C21B8FF447FFF8063763B58FB94FDB1" authorityName="PERIS, DAVIS ET DELCLOS" authorityYear="2014" box="[1077,1129,539,560]" class="Insecta" family="Nemonychidae" genus="Arra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9551F6E447FFF8063763B58FB94FDB1" box="[1077,1129,539,560]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Arra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is Latin for ‘deposit’, and is treated as feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EC37C447FFF8064653BCFFC52FD20" blockId="3.[806,1328,652,704]" box="[806,943,652,673]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">
<emphasis id="B9551F6E447FFF8064653BCFFC52FD20" box="[806,943,652,673]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">
<typeStatus id="549A7DDE447FFF8064653BCFFCA7FD20" box="[806,858,652,673]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EC37C447FFF8064653BE9FACDFD3E" blockId="3.[806,1328,652,704]" box="[806,1328,682,704]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">
<taxonomicName id="4C21B8FF447FFF8064653BE9FB32FD41" authority="Peris, Davis et Delclos" authorityName="Peris, Davis et Delclos" authorityYear="2014" box="[806,1231,682,704]" class="Insecta" family="Nemonychidae" genus="Arra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="legalovi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9551F6E447FFF8064653BE9FC40FD3E" box="[806,957,682,703]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Arra legalovi</emphasis>
Peris, Davis et Delclòs
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A266A215447FFF80639A3BE9FACDFD3E" box="[1241,1328,682,703]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EC37C447FFF8064653BBEFC6BFC93" blockId="3.[806,1422,765,1183]" box="[806,918,765,786]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">
<emphasis id="B9551F6E447FFF8064653BBEFC6BFC93" box="[806,918,765,786]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EC37C447FFF8064653A58FC85FB1E" blockId="3.[806,1422,765,1183]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Long rostrum, apex widened, similar in width to forehead (dorsal width between middle of compound eyes); compound eyes large, not separated by more than one compound eye diameter dorsally; antennae with a very loose club of three antennomeres; seventh funicular article (antennomere 8) slightly smaller than preceding antennomeres; pronotal margins subacute, carinate; procoxae positioned near posterior margin of prosternum; apical tibial spurs 2–2–2; pro- and mesotarsi with tarsomeres 1 to 4 slightly lobed ventrally; metatarsi appear to have four tarsomeres because of partially fused tarsomeres 4 and 5, but separated by a suture.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EC37C447FFF8064653D9EFC5AFB73" blockId="3.[806,1350,1245,1297]" box="[806,935,1245,1266]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">
<emphasis id="B9551F6E447FFF8064653D9EFC5AFB73" box="[806,935,1245,1266]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9EC37C447FFF8064653DB8FABBFA91" blockId="3.[806,1350,1245,1297]" box="[806,1350,1275,1297]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">
Refer to specific description below (
<emphasis id="B9551F6E447FFF8063863DB8FACBFA91" box="[1221,1334,1275,1296]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">vide infra</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
